Lacey Spears of Kentucky was found guilty last month of second-degree murder in the death of Garnett-Paul Spears at a suburban New York hospital . 
  Spears of Scottsville was spared the maximum 25 years to life . 
  She chronicled her son Garnett's illnesses on a personal blog called 'Garnett's Journey' and other social media . 
  She was convicted by a jury in White Plains, New York, in his 2014 death at Westchester Medical Center . 
  The New York judge said she suffers from a mental illness and said the crime was still 'unfathomable in its cruelty'